authors.evidence: A total of 158 right-handed subjects (age range 18–34, 73 women) were recruited from the research participation pool maintained by Princeton University

sample_size_n.evidence: For Experiment 4, we did not have a salient comparable analysis with which to conduct an a priori power analysis (i.e., regression weights on generalization probe distance vs. movement); however, in a previous study where we modeled generalization, we used a sample of 15 subjects. Thus, we opted to use 36 subjects in total (18 per group), a number which allowed for symmetric counterbalancing according to the task design.
